@codeblue122 you are using an [old version of Podman](https://github.com/containers/podman/releases/tag/v4.9.2). Is there any chance to use a more recent one (5.x)? FWIW I was able to run the scenario using a remote linux server running podman v5.4.1.

Also, you have reported the extension version on the local machine (v0.401), but the version of the extension running remotely is relevant here.

And please provide the full output of the command `podman info` ran on the remote host.

With home path set to tmp the container actually builds and runs,
So issue cant be one we are suspecting, its some wrong config in my devcontainer.json

"containerEnv": {
  "HOME": "/tmp/vscode"}
